  "ai_preview": {
    "text": "**Croatia's bouncing back after a shellacking, Ghana's hunting for momentum — this is a third-round slugfest with real stakes.** 🔥 The Croats have won two of their last three but can't shake that 4-2 drubbing to England. Ghana mixed draws with a crucial 1-0 win over Panama and won't roll over.\n\nCroatia's got the pedigree here, but Ghana's midfield engine — anchored by **T. Partey** and **J. Ayew** — can't be slept on. The real battle will be whether **A. Kramarić** and **M. Pašalić** can unlock Ghana's compact 4-4-1 shape, or if **A. Semenyo** and **K. Sulemana** create chaos on the break.\n\nKey storylines:\n\n- **Croatia's defensive tweaks** without D. Ćaleta-Car test how **J. Gvardiol** and **J. Šutalo** hold the line against Ghana's quick counters\n- **Ghana's set-piece threat** — T. Partey's precision and aerial duels could trouble even a solid Croatian backline\n- **Budimir's hold-up play** in the **A. Budimir** role will be crucial; Ghana's **G. Mensah** and **A. Djiku** are no joke defensively\n\nExpected lineups:\n\n- **Croatia**: D. Livaković, J. Šutalo, J. Gvardiol, L. Vušković, I. Perišić, P. Sučić, A. Kramarić, M. Pašalić, P. Musa, A. Budimir\n- **Ghana**: B. Asare, J. A. Adjetey, G. Mensah, A. Djiku, A. Semenyo, C. Yirenkyi, T. Partey, J. Ayew, K. Sulemana\n\nBest picks:\n\n- **Total Goals 1.5**: Over 1.5 goals\n\nPrediction: **Croatia 2–1 Ghana** — the Croats edge it on class, but Ghana makes them sweat. ⚽",
